post_text:
There are many activities going on this week. Just a reminder to check the website for opposing schools' COVID Guidelines.

These are a few of the major guidelines to follow:
- Tuesday Volleyball at Nebraska City - Must be on Pass List (Limit of 6 per player) and masks required.
- Thursday Volleyball Triangular Home - Mask required for all spectators due to multiple schools in the building.
- Friday Football at Sutton - Only family members on the player's pass list may attend due to Sutton's restrictions. Each player gets 4 family members on their pass list.
- Saturday Volleyball @ Weeping Water - Masks required and only immediate family members can attend.
-Saturday Cross County - Mask required for all spectators.

We will continue to post restrictions and guidelines on the school website.

7-12 Sports Physical Information:

Due to Covid-19, the only students that need to get a sport physical this year are students entering grades 7 & 9 or any student that did not get a physical last year and wants to participate in sports this year.

All incoming 7-12 Grade students planning on participating in any sports this upcoming year will still need to fill out the school required forms. Those forms can be found on the WC webpage under the Athletic Forms link.

Any questions please email jeff.hatcliff@wilberclatonia.org

Wilber-Clatonia Elementary School: Ms. Jane knows all of our families. She has an amazing memory that she knows student and parent names and recognizes everyone when they come into the office, present and past students! She has a wonderful historical perspective of the building and community. Ms. Jane takes care of all of us in the building. Any time that anyone needs something, we always go to Jane because we know that she will help us with whatever is needed. She always has a smile on her face and answers the phone so positive. She is a tremendous asset to the Wolverine community.
We ❤ our Administrative Professional. We love you Ms. Jane, so help me shower her on this special day! #AdministrativeProfessionalsDay

post_text: On Wednesday, April 1st the WC staff will be on a "parade" throughout Wilber and Clatonia. They will be following the attached maps to hit as many streets to see as many students as possible. We will be leaving the high school parking lot at 1:00 PM and look to enter Clatonia around 1:50. Students and families we invite you to come to the end of your driveway or down the street to wave at us! While all of us want to maintain social distancing recommendations: please remember to stand 6 feet or more away from other families, stay on the curb for everyone's safety and please wave, hold up a sign, or watch. We are all excited to see our students and want them to know we are missing them! #WOLVERINESTRONG

Fairbury Journal-News
February 22 at 9:01 PM ·

Wilber-Clatonia's Colby Homolka (138) and Eric Escobar (285) garnered state medals on Saturday at the state wrestling tournament.

Homolka (138) placed fourth in Class C as the seventh ranked wrestler coming into the tourney. It was Homolka's first state appearance. Escobar, a senior, placed sixth at heavyweight to end his career as a Wolverine wrestle.

The duo led Wilber-Clatonia to a 15th place finish as a team out of the 60 teams who competed in Class C. All eight Wilber-Clatonia qualifiers won at least one match.

See story in Wednesday's FJN. See more photos in a photo album on the FJN Facebook page in coming days.
